The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on Wednesday won four more local government areas in Rivers state as the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) continues the collation of March 9 gubernatorial election. At the resumed collation of the results of the state’s governorship elections in Port Harcourt today, the PDP has won Obio-Akpor, Ogu/Bolo, Asari Toru and Degema LGAs. Earlier on Tuesday, the African Action Congress (AAC) governorship candidate in Rivers state, Engr. Biokpomabo Awara, floored his arch rival, Nyesom Wike of the PDP in two local government areas, namely Oyibo and Akuku-Toru LGAs. See the FULL RESULTS of the additional four local governments announced today below: Obio-Akpor Local Government AAC – 7,495 PDP – 281,164  Ogu/Bolo Local Government AAC  – 814 PDP  – 11,855  Asari Toru Local Government AAC – 18,945 PDP – 32,172  Degema Local Government AAC – 5,071 PDP – 12,133 Rivers: Wike leads in 12 LGs as collation continues today Atiku takes early lead in Rivers Rivers governorship: Awara floors Wike in two LGAs, as INEC collates poll results of 10 LGAs